50|$|Tornadoes {{have been}} {{recorded}} on all continents except Antarctica and are most common in the middle latitudes where conditions are often favorable for <b>convective</b> <b>storm</b> development. The United States has the most tornadoes of any country, {{as well as the}} strongest and most violent tornadoes. A large portion of these tornadoes form in an area of the central United States popularly known as Tornado Alley. Other areas of the world that have frequent tornadoes include significant portions of Europe, South Africa, Bangladesh, parts of Argentina, Uruguay, and southern and southeast Brazil, New Zealand, and far eastern Asia.|$|E
